2.01	Calvin_murphy	Calvin Murphy	Calvin Murphy (born May 9, 1948) is a retired American professional basketball player who played as a guard for the NBA's San Diego/Houston Rockets from 1970-1983. He is a former member of the Houston Rockets' broadcast team. He was also the host of ESPN Radio's The Calvin Murphy Show. Standing at a height of 5 feet 9 inches (1.75 m), Murphy has the distinction of being the shortest player inducted into the Basketball Hall of Fame.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Calvin_Murphy_1.jpg/200px-Calvin_Murphy_1.jpg
